verbose_text: SCr level, glycosylated hemoglobin (HbA1c) level, daily urine protein excretion, daily protein intake (DPI), mean arterial pressure (MAP), cholesterol level (including high-density lipoprotein, HDL and low-density lipoprotein, LDL), and triglyceride (TG) level were measured using an autoanalyzer system (model 736; Hitachi, Tokyo, Japan) at the beginning and end of the study and every 6 months during the 24-month clinical observation period.
